    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "annot-sheets-b5-20260718",
      "x": 70,
      "y": 1600,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 140,
      "text": "AS-BUILT 2026-07-18 (agent revisions, mega-run B5): ChatRunCreateRequest gains OPTIONAL\nreviseSheetId (the composer chip's target): the completed reply persists as a NEW revision on\nthat sheet { editSource: 'agent', instruction: <the user message> } instead of spawning a new\nsheet; the persisted assistant turn BACK-REFERENCES it (metadata sheetId/revisionId/\nrevisionNumber) so the read path derives no second sheet and model-bound history DROPS the\ncarrier turn (the origin turn already carries the latest revision - locked decision 7). The\nreply_summary notification gains optional revision (1-based ordinal) for the transcript's\n'Revisão N' card framing. Unknown reviseSheetId falls back to fresh-sheet behavior.",
      "originalText": "AS-BUILT 2026-07-18 (agent revisions, mega-run B5): ChatRunCreateRequest gains OPTIONAL\nreviseSheetId (the composer chip's target): the completed reply persists as a NEW revision on\nthat sheet { editSource: 'agent', instruction: <the user message> } instead of spawning a new\nsheet; the persisted assistant turn BACK-REFERENCES it (metadata sheetId/revisionId/\nrevisionNumber) so the read path derives no second sheet and model-bound history DROPS the\ncarrier turn (the origin turn already carries the latest revision - locked decision 7). The\nreply_summary notification gains optional revision (1-based ordinal) for the transcript's\n'Revisão N' card framing. Unknown reviseSheetId falls back to fresh-sheet behavior.",
      "rawText": "AS-BUILT 2026-07-18 (agent revisions, mega-run B5): ChatRunCreateRequest gains OPTIONAL\nreviseSheetId (the composer chip's target): the completed reply persists as a NEW revision on\nthat sheet { editSource: 'agent', instruction: <the user message> } instead of spawning a new\nsheet; the persisted assistant turn BACK-REFERENCES it (metadata sheetId/revisionId/\nrevisionNumber) so the read path derives no second sheet and model-bound history DROPS the\ncarrier turn (the origin turn already carries the latest revision - locked decision 7). The\nreply_summary notification gains optional revision (1-based ordinal) for the transcript's\n'Revisão N' card framing. Unknown reviseSheetId falls back to fresh-sheet behavior.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
