    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "annot-usage-events-c2-20260718",
      "x": 70,
      "y": 1760,
      "width": 780,
      "height": 122.5,
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "strokeColor": "#b45309",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 47210919,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 815263106,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": null,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "text": "AS-BUILT C2 2026-07-18 (voice metering, mega-run 20260717-190134): usage_events - the NON-TOKEN\nsibling of token_events. One doc per (source, session), _id = <source>:<orgId>:<sessionId>, org+user attributed\n(orgId + billeeUserId from the verified token), counters an open map keyed by canonical counter names:\nvoice_stt_ms + voice_tts_chars as SEPARATE counters, NO token conversion. Written ONLY by\nbilling/tracker.ts (recordUsageCounters, the single metering writer). Part D assistant-turn metering\nadds a counter key under its own source - same collection, no migration. activity_logs rows gain\noptional usageCounts (counter names verbatim - A5 vocabulary rule 3), emitted on the Registo read.",
      "rawText": "AS-BUILT C2 2026-07-18 (voice metering, mega-run 20260717-190134): usage_events - the NON-TOKEN\nsibling of token_events. One doc per (source, session), _id = <source>:<orgId>:<sessionId>, org+user attributed\n(orgId + billeeUserId from the verified token), counters an open map keyed by canonical counter names:\nvoice_stt_ms + voice_tts_chars as SEPARATE counters, NO token conversion. Written ONLY by\nbilling/tracker.ts (recordUsageCounters, the single metering writer). Part D assistant-turn metering\nadds a counter key under its own source - same collection, no migration. activity_logs rows gain\noptional usageCounts (counter names verbatim - A5 vocabulary rule 3), emitted on the Registo read.",
      "originalText": "AS-BUILT C2 2026-07-18 (voice metering, mega-run 20260717-190134): usage_events - the NON-TOKEN\nsibling of token_events. One doc per (source, session), _id = <source>:<orgId>:<sessionId>, org+user attributed\n(orgId + billeeUserId from the verified token), counters an open map keyed by canonical counter names:\nvoice_stt_ms + voice_tts_chars as SEPARATE counters, NO token conversion. Written ONLY by\nbilling/tracker.ts (recordUsageCounters, the single metering writer). Part D assistant-turn metering\nadds a counter key under its own source - same collection, no migration. activity_logs rows gain\noptional usageCounts (counter names verbatim - A5 vocabulary rule 3), emitted on the Registo read."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "annot-portal-e1-20260718",
      "x": 70,
      "y": 1920,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 160,
      "text": "AS-BUILT E1 2026-07-18 (portal connectors, mega-run 20260717-190134): documentos/eventos rows\ngain an ORIGEM='portal' variant, written by the shared/ PortalDocument/PortalEvent contract (the\nFIRST legal descriptor that is not z.unknown()) via legal/portal.ts attachPortalDocument/\nattachPortalEvent - no new collection, same usr.<owner> spine DocumentosTab.jsx/CronologiaTab.jsx\nalready render. documentos gains source/subjectIds/retrievedAt/parsed?; eventos gains source/kind/\nsubjectRef/observedAt/payload - flat, round-tripping back into the shared shape for GET /api/legal/\nportal (header-scoped, same tier as citius/calculos). Attach is org-checked (getOwnerOrgId vs the\ncaller's orgId) - the first org check this plane has needed. activity_logs gains portal.document.\nretrieved / portal.watch.hit rows (A5 vocabulary). Signed-in follow-up connectors EXTEND these\nshapes via passthrough, never redesign them.",
      "rawText": "AS-BUILT E1 2026-07-18 (portal connectors, mega-run 20260717-190134): documentos/eventos rows\ngain an ORIGEM='portal' variant, written by the shared/ PortalDocument/PortalEvent contract (the\nFIRST legal descriptor that is not z.unknown()) via legal/portal.ts attachPortalDocument/\nattachPortalEvent - no new collection, same usr.<owner> spine DocumentosTab.jsx/CronologiaTab.jsx\nalready render. documentos gains source/subjectIds/retrievedAt/parsed?; eventos gains source/kind/\nsubjectRef/observedAt/payload - flat, round-tripping back into the shared shape for GET /api/legal/\nportal (header-scoped, same tier as citius/calculos). Attach is org-checked (getOwnerOrgId vs the\ncaller's orgId) - the first org check this plane has needed. activity_logs gains portal.document.\nretrieved / portal.watch.hit rows (A5 vocabulary). Signed-in follow-up connectors EXTEND these\nshapes via passthrough, never redesign them.",
      "originalText": "AS-BUILT E1 2026-07-18 (portal connectors, mega-run 20260717-190134): documentos/eventos rows\ngain an ORIGEM='portal' variant, written by the shared/ PortalDocument/PortalEvent contract (the\nFIRST legal descriptor that is not z.unknown()) via legal/portal.ts attachPortalDocument/\nattachPortalEvent - no new collection, same usr.<owner> spine DocumentosTab.jsx/CronologiaTab.jsx\nalready render. documentos gains source/subjectIds/retrievedAt/parsed?; eventos gains source/kind/\nsubjectRef/observedAt/payload - flat, round-tripping back into the shared shape for GET /api/legal/\nportal (header-scoped, same tier as citius/calculos). Attach is org-checked (getOwnerOrgId vs the\ncaller's orgId) - the first org check this plane has needed. activity_logs gains portal.document.\nretrieved / portal.watch.hit rows (A5 vocabulary). Signed-in follow-up connectors EXTEND these\nshapes via passthrough, never redesign them.",
