      "id": "annot-portal-e2e3-20260718-e4",
      "x": 70,
      "y": 2304,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 180,
      "text": "AS-BUILT E4 2026-07-18 (insolvência watcher, mega-run 20260717-190134): NEW satellite collection citius_watches on the usr.<owner> spine - row {processoId, subjects[] (NIFs/names), lastSeen, seenRefs[]} (ordinary dossiê data, no secrets). pollInsolvencyWatches(app,processoId,actor,deps) fetches the Citius publico insolvencia list (SSRF-guarded, config base URL) for the watched subjects, diffs vs seenRefs, and for each NEW publication emits a PortalEvent kind watch.hit via attachPortalEvent + advances seenRefs (idempotent: a seen ref never re-emits). No scheduler wired (public-tier has no cron); operator/cron calls the fn, POST /api/legal/portal/insolvency/poll (requireLegalSuiteApp tier) runs one cycle for a dossiê. Org-checked; audit rows refs-only.",
      "rawText": "AS-BUILT E2/E3 2026-07-18 (certidão connectors, mega-run 20260717-190134): the FIRST connector\nto write through E1's shapes. legal/portal-connectors.ts fetches by access code (certidao-comercial/\npredial/civil - civil lands at the SAME shape, not degraded) behind config.ts's PortalConnectorsConfig\nbase URLs, guardedFetch-SSRF-guarded by default, injected fetchImpl test seam (citius.ts discipline;\ndecodeHtml/cellText shared out to portal-html.ts). POST /api/legal/portal/certidao (same header-scoped\ntier + PORTAL_ALLOWED_APPS allowlist as GET /api/legal/portal) saves the bytes via apps/app-files.ts's\nsaveAppFileBlob (an INJECTED seam - legal/ never imports apps/ directly) then calls BOTH\nattachPortalDocument (a documentos row) and attachPortalEvent(kind:'document.retrieved') (an eventos\nrow, so a certidão retrieval also renders in Cronologia) - no partial write: a bad/expired code or an\nunreachable portal returns a clean PT-PT 503 (citius.ts's looksUnavailable idiom) before any blob is\nsaved or row written. accessCode is an ordinary dossiê field - never persisted, logged, or audited.",
